description.text:
### Tested versions

- 4.2 stable
- 4.3 stable
- 4.4 beta1

I can't recall this ever working correctly 🫤

### System information

🪟 Windows 11 - 🤖 Godot 4.4 beta1

### Issue description

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/18b5a500-7f43-445f-bdc9-22c0e109efdd)

When using an external editor (i.e. VSCode), clicking the stack frame dose nuttin @ all 😢

### Steps to reproduce

## Internal Editor: 👍

1. Disable External Editor
2. Run project
3. Get error
4. Click Stack Frame
5. Goes to line 👍✅

## External Editor: ❌

1. Set External Editor in Editor settings ([see docs](https://docs.godotengine.org/en/stable/tutorials/editor/external_editor.html))
2. Run project
3. Get error
4. Click Stack Frame
5. Nothing 😔⚠️

### Minimal reproduction project (MRP)

📂 [StackFrameMRP.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/18525615/StackFrameMRP.zip) 📂

